      <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1825-12_page01.jpg"/>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="image1.jpg"/>
            <!--filenames for photos associated with this letter. Example: <pb n="1" facs="image1.jpg image2.jpg image3.jpg"/> -->
            <opener>
               <dateline>Dec<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> 24<hi rend="superscript">h</hi> 1825
                  <name type="place" ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworths Town</name>
                  <lb/>
                  <date when="1825-12-24"/>December 24, 1825.</dateline>
               <salute>
                  <persName>
                     Sir
                  </persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p> 
               I have just seen an <choice>
                  <orig>ad-<lb/>
               vertisement</orig>
                  <reg>advertisement</reg>
               </choice> in the <title ref="./Workography.xml#Morni1">
                  <choice>
                     <orig>Morn<lb/>
               ing</orig>
                     <reg>Morning</reg>
                  </choice> Chronicle</title> of a new<lb/>
               Pocket book called the<lb/>
               <title ref="./Workography.xml#Janus1">Janus</title> published I think<lb/>
               in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edinburgh_STK">Edinburgh</placeName> in which<lb/>
               I see my <del>essay[</del>
               <title ref="./Workography.xml#Though1">"Thoughts<lb/>
               on Bores by a Bore</title> is<lb/>
               inserted - I wish you<lb/>
               to know that I did not<lb/>
               know till I saw that<lb/>
               advertisement that<lb/>
               this essay of mine was<lb/>
               to appear in what you<lb/>
               may consider as a<lb/>
               rival publication - In<lb/>
               truth I did not know<lb/>
               the existence of this<lb/>
               publication -<lb/>
            </p>
            <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1825-12_page02.jpg"/>
            <p>I am not so vain as to<lb/>
               conceive that such a trifle<lb/>
               as my contribution could<lb/>
               be of any consequence<lb/>
               one way or other to either<lb/>
               of the Publications but<lb/>
               I wish you to know that<lb/>
               I meant you handsomely<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>The friend to whom I<lb/>
               gave the <hi rend="underline">
                  <title ref="./Workography.xml#Though1">bores</title>
               </hi> disposed<lb/>
               of them as he thought <choice>
                  <orig>pro<lb/>
               per</orig>
                  <reg>proper</reg>
               </choice> -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>I am anxious to have<lb/>
               back again the account<lb/>
               I sent to your <title ref="./Workography.xml#Frien1">"Friendships<lb/>
               offering"</title> of the 4 Ex-Presidents<lb/>
               of America if your editor<lb/>
               has not inserted them -<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               With good wishes for<lb/>
               your success I am<lb/>
               Sir<lb/>
               very truly yours<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p>If any thing of mine is<lb/>
                  <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1825-12_page03.jpg"/>

               in your pocket book of<lb/>
               this year &amp; if you wish<lb/>
               to send me one you<lb/>
               can do so by enclosing<lb/>
               it directed to<lb/>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Miss Edgeworth</persName>
                  <lb/>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworths Town</placeName>
                  <lb/>
               under cover to<lb/>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ParsL1">The Earl of Rosse</persName>
                  <lb/>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Parsonstown-House_IE">Parson's Town<lb/>
               Ireland</placeName>.<lb/>
               </p>
            </postscript>
            <note place="bottom">"Tales various" <unclear>London</unclear>
            </note>
            <lb/>
            <closer><!--Use the <closer> element again to hold Address Leaf information.-->
               <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1825-12_page04.jpg"/>
               <address>
                  <addrLine>M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> L. Relfe - Bookseller</addrLine>
                  <lb/>
                  <addrLine>Cornhill</addrLine>
                  <lb/>
                  <!--Include any text written on the address leaf; use a separate "addrLine" for each line and indicate line breaks. -->
               </address>
            </closer>
